title: Appointments to Community Investment and Inclusion Fund Committee (CIIF)
content_text:
p>The Government announced today (April 1) the re-appointment of the chairperson, 
Dr Wu Wai-yung, Raymond to the Community Investment and Inclusion Fund (CIIF) 
Committee.  Ms Sophia Kao, an incumbent member of the committee since its establishment 
three years ago, was appointed as the vice-chairperson.  In addition, five new members were appointed to the committee. They are Mr Chow 
Ching-lam, Tony; Mr Kwan Chuk-fai; Dr Lam Ching-choi; Ms Lau Ka-shi, Betsy; and

Mr Ng Chi-wing, Stephen.  The above re-appointment/appointments will take effect from today (April 1) for 
a term of three years.  Mr Chow is an appointed district councillor of Wong Tai Sin District as well as 
the chairman/president of a number of territory-wide industry organisations. 
Despite his background as a businessman, Mr Chow has rich experience in 
organising youth activities at district levels.  Mr Kwan is the general manager (corporate communication) of NWS Holdings Ltd. He

also serves on the Sub-Committee on Promotion of Corporate Volunteering of the 
Social Welfare Department (SWD) and has been an active member in promoting 
volunteering work in the business sector.  Dr Lam is the chief executive of the Haven of Hope Christian Service which 
provides welfare and health services. He is also a member of the Sai Kung 
District Council with hands-on experience in mobilising support from local 
groups in developing community projects.  Ms Lau is the managing director and chief executive officer of the Bank

Consortium Trust Company Limited. She is familiar with the CIIF and the concepts 
of social capital.  Mr Ng is the community services secretary of Tung Wah Group of Hospitals which 
has first-hand experience in community projects. He is also a member of SWD's 
Sub-Committee on Promotion of Corporate Volunteering and has previously served 
in some other welfare-related committees such as the Social Welfare Advisory 
Committee.  In this new round of appointments, seven incumbent members have been

Committee.  In this new round of appointments, seven incumbent members have been 
re-appointed for a term of two years. They are Dr Chan Sze-tong, Thomas; Dr Kwok 
Kin-fun, Joseph; Dr Leung Man-kit, Christopher; Mr Tso Kai-lok; Mr Wong Siu-yee; 
Ms Yu Sau-chu, Jessie; and Prof Yuen Tsang Woon-ki, Angelina.  The Secretary for Health, Welfare and Food, Dr York Chow, noted the 
appointment/re-appointment exercise involved representatives from a variety of

appointment/re-appointment exercise involved representatives from a variety of 
social backgrounds. He looked forward to their contribution to the committee and 
the continued promotion of social capital in Hong Kong.  Dr Chow also thanked the three outgoing members - Ms Fang Meng-sang, Christine; 
Mrs Lee Cheung Wai-mi, Julita; and Mrs Ng Wong Yee-man, Gloria - for their 
contribution to the work of the committee during their tenure.  The $300-million CIIF was established in 2002 to encourage mutual concern and

help among people, to further develop community support network and to promote 
community participation. The CIIF committee is tasked with considering and 
approving funding for applications and advising the Government on the

development of social capital.
